First Pattern¶

Computation = Operations on (Data Structures)¶

Python:¶

  • Operations on Collections

Pandas:¶

  • Operations on Data Frames (fundamental data structure of data science)

Numpy¶

  • Vectorized Operations: Matrices and Vectors.
  • Fun Fact: Matrices act as operators or functions.

Functions¶

  • Functions are "first class". Functions accept functions as arguments and produce functions as output.

For the first pattern you will be working back and forth at four levels of abstraction: python, pandas, numpy, and linear algebra. And sometimes a spot of calculus.

What is Machine Learning?¶

We use computers to carry out tasks. The computer uses an algorithm to perform the task.¶

For some tasks a human programmer is able to write the algorithm, or step-by-step instructions.¶

In [46]:
image('programmer.png')
Out[46]:

It turns out that for some tasks it is impossible or impractical for humans to explicitly write the algorithm.¶

In [47]:
image("frustrated.png")
Out[47]:

In machine learning the computer "learns" the algorithm from data.¶

"Machine learning is a field of study that gives computers the ability to learn without being explicitly programmed." --Arthur Samuel (1901-1990).

The essence of supervised machine learning is prediction.¶

Simple Linear Regression Key Ideas¶

  • Key Idea 1: In SLR, a single feature variable is used to predict a single target variable.

  • Key Idea 2:: In SLR, the feature and target variables are both continuous.

  • Key Idea 3: In SLR, the feature and target variables are represented as vectors for the purpose of computation.

  • Key Idea 4: In SLR, the model is a straight line, also called the regression line and the line of best fit.

  • Key Idea 5: Each machine learning model is specified by its parameters. SLR has two model parameters: $\beta_0$ and $\beta_1$. $\beta_0$ is the intercept of the regression line and $\beta_1$ is the slope.

  • Key Idea 6: In SLR, a key metric for evaluating model accuracy is R2 (pronounced "R squared").
